A memorial service will be held to honour former Rangers and Scotland defender Colin Jackson who died aged 68 following a battle of leukaemia.Rangers FC announced on their website that the London-born star's funeral will be a private service for close family members only.A memorial service, however, will be in the Ibrox Suite at the stadium on Saturday, June 20 at 11.30am.The footballer sadly lost his battle with cancer and passed away peacefully with his family last weekend.